headline: As insurers axe Medicare plans, here's what advisors should know
summary: As major insurers reduce Medicare Advantage benefits and exit markets, retirees face higher costs and limited options. Advisors need to understand the implications for retirement planning.

headline: CVS Q2 Deep Dive: Pharmacy Strength and Aetna Recovery Drive Guidance Boost
summary: Diversified healthcare company CVS Health (NYSE:CVS) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 8.4% year on year to $98.92 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.81 per share was 23.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
